<subSubSection pageId="36" pageNumber="337" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="36.[151,1436,1711,2024]" pageId="36" pageNumber="337">
This subspecies was described from Grande 
<collectingCountry box="[670,760,1712,1736]" name="Comoros" pageId="36" pageNumber="337">Comore</collectingCountry>
(Njazidja, 
<collectingCountry box="[893,997,1712,1736]" name="Comoros" pageId="36" pageNumber="337">Comoros</collectingCountry>
) (
<bibRefCitation author="Oberthur" box="[1022,1195,1711,1736]" firstAuthor="Oberthur" pageId="36" pageNumber="337" pagination="177" refId="ref31960" refString="Oberthur, C. (1916) II. - Hesperidae. Observations sur une centurie d'especes de Lepidopteres rhopaloceres malgaches. Etudes de lepidopterologie comparee, par Charles Oberthur, 11, 177 - 244, plates 136 - 137." type="journal article" year="1916">
Oberthür 
<number box="[1135,1195,1711,1736]" pageId="36" pageNumber="337" value="1916.0">1916</number>
</bibRefCitation>
), and also occurs on Anjouan (Nzwani, 
<collectingCountry box="[366,470,1748,1772]" name="Comoros" pageId="36" pageNumber="337">Comoros</collectingCountry>
) (
<bibRefCitation author="Turlin" box="[493,629,1747,1772]" firstAuthor="Turlin" pageId="36" pageNumber="337" pagination="197" refId="ref32982" refString="Turlin, B. (1995) Faune lepidopterique de l'Archipel des Comores (Ocean Indien). (Rhopaloceres, Sphingidae, Attacidae) (6). Lambillionea, 95, 197 - 210." type="journal article" year="1995">
Turlin 
<number box="[572,629,1747,1772]" pageId="36" pageNumber="337" value="1995.0">1995</number>
</bibRefCitation>
) and 
<collectingCountry box="[692,785,1748,1772]" name="Mayotte" pageId="36" pageNumber="337">Mayotte</collectingCountry>
(Overseas Department of 
<collectingCountry box="[1084,1162,1748,1772]" name="France" pageId="36" pageNumber="337">France</collectingCountry>
) (ABRI collection), and can be expected to occur on other islands of the Comoro archipelago where its food plants occur. ABRI collectors have reared this subspecies many times since 
<number box="[663,719,1820,1844]" pageId="36" pageNumber="337" value="1978.0">1978</number>
from 
<taxonomicName box="[788,899,1819,1844]" class="Liliopsida" family="Asparagaceae" genus="Dracaena" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="36" pageNumber="337" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="reflexa">
<emphasis box="[788,899,1819,1844]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="337">D. reflexa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
on Grande 
<collectingCountry box="[1030,1123,1820,1844]" name="Comoros" pageId="36" pageNumber="337">Comore</collectingCountry>
, Anjouan and 
<collectingCountry box="[1285,1382,1820,1844]" name="Mayotte" pageId="36" pageNumber="337">Mayotte</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="38" lastPageNumber="339" pageId="36" pageNumber="337" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="36.[151,1436,1711,2024]" lastBlockId="37.[151,1436,151,285]" lastPageId="37" lastPageNumber="338" pageId="36" pageNumber="337">
We also show photographs of caterpillars and a pupa collected on 
<taxonomicName box="[939,1050,1855,1880]" class="Liliopsida" family="Asparagaceae" genus="Dracaena" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="36" pageNumber="337" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="reflexa">
<emphasis box="[939,1050,1855,1880]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="337">D. reflexa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, Grande 
<collectingCountry box="[1153,1246,1856,1880]" name="Comoros" pageId="36" pageNumber="337">Comore</collectingCountry>
, mostly taken by Alain Gauthier (
<figureCitation box="[340,457,1891,1916]" captionStart="FIGURE 34" captionStartId="38.[151,250,1580,1602]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,269,1554]" captionTargetId="figure@38.[151,1436,267,1555]" captionTargetPageId="38" captionText="FIGURE 34. Early stages of Artitropa erinnys comoranum, collected on Dracaena reflexa, Grande Comore, Comoro Islands; 1 – 4, final instar caterpillar; 5, pupa. 1, 3 – 5, Moroni, 3 – 9 Sep 2014 [© Alain Gauthier]; 2, 13 Apr 2004 [TCEC]. 1, dorsal / dorsolateral view in shelter; 35 mm; 2, detail of head, anterior view; 3, detail of head, anterodorsolateral view; 4, detail of head, anterodorsolateral view; 5, newly formed pupa, dorsolateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/253567/files/figure.png" pageId="36" pageNumber="337">
Figure 
<number box="[425,457,1892,1916]" pageId="36" pageNumber="337" value="34.0">34</number>
</figureCitation>
). The head of the final instar caterpillar collected by TCEC (Figure 
<number box="[1262,1313,1892,1916]" pageId="36" pageNumber="337" value="34.2">34.2</number>
) is yellow brown, with the adfrontals and frons concolorous; just two relatively small black spots on the face on each epicranium, comparable to the form of the caterpillar 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Karsch" authorityYear="1896" box="[784,925,1963,1988]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Artitropa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="337" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="erinnys" subSpecies="ehlersi">
<emphasis box="[784,925,1963,1988]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="337">A. e. ehlersi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from Nguru Mountains (Figure 
<number box="[1308,1360,1964,1988]" pageId="36" pageNumber="337" value="28.3">28.3</number>
– 
<number box="[1376,1390,1964,1988]" pageId="36" pageNumber="337" value="4.0">4</number>
). In contrast, one caterpillar photographed by Alain Gauthier, has three additional dark dashes dorsally on the adfrontals and frons, comparable to the caterpillar attributed to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Karsch" authorityYear="1896" box="[874,1011,151,176]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Artitropa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="338" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="erinnys" subSpecies="ehlersi">
<emphasis box="[874,1011,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="338">A. e. ehlersi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the 
<collectingCountry box="[1125,1198,152,176]" name="Kenya" pageId="37" pageNumber="338">Kenya</collectingCountry>
Coast (Figure 
<number box="[1371,1423,152,176]" pageId="37" pageNumber="338" value="28.1">28.1</number>
), while the other has more strongly developed markings on the adfrontals and frons, and lateral spots on the epicranium, comparable to the caterpillars of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Riley" authorityYear="1925" box="[677,818,224,248]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Artitropa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="338" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="erinnys" subSpecies="nyasae">
<emphasis box="[677,818,224,248]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="338">A. e. nyasae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from Ruo Gorge (Figure 
<number box="[1120,1171,224,248]" pageId="37" pageNumber="338" value="29.1">29.1</number>
– 
<number box="[1188,1202,224,248]" pageId="37" pageNumber="338" value="2.0">2</number>
). The newly formed pupa (Figure 
<number box="[302,352,260,285]" pageId="37" pageNumber="338" value="34.5">34.5</number>
) has no markings.
</paragraph>
<caption httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/253566/files/figure.png" pageId="37" pageNumber="338" targetBox="[151,1436,361,1739]" targetPageId="37">
<paragraph blockId="37.[151,1436,1788,1903]" pageId="37" pageNumber="338">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,289,1788,1810]" pageId="37" pageNumber="338">FIGURE 33.</emphasis>
Caterpillar, pupa and adult of 
<taxonomicName authority="erinnys" authorityName="erinnys Trimen" authorityYear="1862" box="[608,867,1789,1811]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Artitropa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="338" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="erinnys" subSpecies="erinnys">
<emphasis box="[608,867,1789,1811]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="338">Artitropa erinnys erinnys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, on 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bos" authorityYear="1992" baseAuthorityName="Haw." box="[914,1143,1788,1811]" class="Liliopsida" family="Asparagaceae" genus="Dracaena" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="37" pageNumber="338" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="aletriformis">
<emphasis box="[914,1143,1788,1811]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="338">Dracaena aletriformis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, Scotburg, Kwa-Zulu Natal, South Africa [SCC]. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[367,405,1819,1841]" pageId="37" pageNumber="338">1–3</emphasis>
, final instar caterpillar: 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[652,665,1819,1841]" pageId="37" pageNumber="338">1</emphasis>
, head, anterodorsal view, 26 Sep 2004; 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1074,1087,1819,1841]" pageId="37" pageNumber="338">2</emphasis>
, dorsolateral view; 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1290,1303,1819,1841]" pageId="37" pageNumber="338">3</emphasis>
, dorsolateral view. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[213,251,1850,1872]" pageId="37" pageNumber="338">4–5</emphasis>
, pupa: 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[332,345,1850,1872]" pageId="37" pageNumber="338">4</emphasis>
, dorsolateral view, 23 Sep 2004; 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[698,710,1850,1872]" pageId="37" pageNumber="338">5</emphasis>
, lateral view, 23 Sep 2004. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1007,1045,1850,1872]" pageId="37" pageNumber="338">7–8</emphasis>
, adult female, 26 Sep 2004: 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1350,1363,1850,1872]" pageId="37" pageNumber="338">7</emphasis>
, upper surface; 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[237,250,1881,1903]" pageId="37" pageNumber="338">8</emphasis>
, under surface.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="37.[151,1436,1947,2008]" lastBlockId="38.[151,1436,151,213]" lastPageId="38" lastPageNumber="339" pageId="37" pageNumber="338">
We have examined images of just three caterpillars in preparing this account, and they show considerable variation, paralleling that found in different populations in mainland Africa. This highlights the need to understand the extent of individual variation in separate populations and subspecies before coming to firm conclusions about the differences observed in the early stages of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Trimen" authorityYear="1862" box="[669,782,188,212]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Artitropa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="38" pageNumber="339" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="erinnys">
<emphasis box="[669,782,188,212]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="339">A. erinnys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
